<a name="Colors in Tables">

<H1>Colors in Tables
</H1>


<P>
<B><U>Question:</U></B>
</P>


<P>
How can I use <A name="index_8_1"></A>color in tables?
</P>


<P>
<B><U>Answer:</U></B>
</P>


<P>
Use the <CODE>\TABLE</CODE> tag with special options:
</P>


<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=80%><TR><TD bgcolor="#e5e5e5"><PRE>
<FONT COLOR="#000000">
 \TABLE{separator=&quot;,&quot; <B>bgcolor</B>=&quot;#CCCCCC&quot; <B>head_bgcolor</B>=yellow}
   Column 1 , Column 2
   value 1  , value 2
   value 3 , value 4
 \END_TABLE
</FONT></PRE></TD></TR></TABLE>


<P>
<B><U>Discussion:</U></B>
</P>


<P>
The above examples yields:
</P>
<TABLE border=2 BGCOLOR="#CCCCCC"><TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="yellow">Column 1</TD><TD BGCOLOR="yellow">Column 2</TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD>value 1</TD><TD>value 2</TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD>value 3</TD><TD>value 4</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P>


<P>

